<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1166,1407]" box="[151,488,1166,1192]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,488,1166,1192]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<number box="[151,188,1166,1191]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="2.2">2.2</number>
. Complex 
<taxonomicName box="[314,488,1167,1192]" class="Insecta" family="Phaneropteridae" genus="Isophya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pavelii">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[314,488,1167,1192]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Isophya pavelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1166,1407]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Moderately stout species. 
<collectingCountry box="[447,503,1203,1227]" name="India" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Hind</collectingCountry>
femora may have single spines. The ovipositor is longer than in the 
<taxonomicName box="[1288,1436,1204,1227]" class="Insecta" family="Phaneropteridae" genus="Isophya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rectipennis">
<emphasis box="[1288,1436,1204,1227]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">I. rectipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex—between 
<number box="[378,392,1239,1263]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="9.0">9</number>
and 
<quantity box="[450,534,1239,1263]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="12.0">12 mm</quantity>
. The complex is characterised by more progressive features—thickened longer CuP, moderately approximated to CuA in males and transition to reticulate venation towards the medial part of tegmina in females; the song consists of groups of syllables or (possibly) isolated syllables with a tendency to grouping (in 
<taxonomicName box="[301,387,1347,1371]" class="Insecta" family="Phaneropteridae" genus="Isophya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ilkazi">
<emphasis box="[301,387,1347,1371]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">I. ilkazi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The complex includes 
<number box="[672,686,1347,1371]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="5.0">5</number>
taxa (
<number box="[759,774,1347,1371]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="4.0">4</number>
species) from the Central and Northwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[1290,1386,1347,1371]" name="Turkey" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
and southeasternmost territory of the Balkan Peninsula (see above).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
